export const questionObj = {"Qtext": "
In the below given figure, it is given that \(\angle IKJ = \angle KLI \). If \(IK = 8 \) cm, and \(IL = 7 \) cm, then find the length of JL
\newline
tikzpicture{}
\newline

", "Steps": [{"id": "s1", "n_params": 0, "step_txt": "Consider the triangles IKJ and ILK , here we have
\[
	\angle JIK = \angle LIK 
\]
\[
	\angle IKJ = \angle KLI 
\]
So, we can write that
\[
	\Delta IKJ \sim \Delta ILK 
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow \frac{IK }{IL } = \frac{IJ }{IK } 
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow \frac{8 }{7 } = \frac{IJ }{8 }
\]
\[
	\Rightarrow IJ = \frac{64 }{7 }
\]
So, now 
\[
	JL = IJ - IL = \frac{64 }{7 } - 7 = \frac{15 }{7 } cm
\]
\newline

"}]}
